## Crew Structure

### Roles per Rig

| Role | Count | Responsibility |
|------|-------|---------------|
| coordinator | 1 | PM, architecture, task routing |
| reviewer | 1 | Code review, QA, merge gating |
| workers | on-demand | All coding, spawned per-task |

### Orchestration Offloading

Patrol agents (witness, refinery, deacon) can run on cheaper LLM backends
via LiteLLM proxy. Set `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` to the LiteLLM endpoint when
spawning patrol agents. Reserve expensive models for human-facing sessions
and strategic work only.

### Design Principle

Keep orchestration overhead minimal. Workers are transient — spawned per-task,
destroyed after completion. The coordinator plans; workers execute. The reviewer
gates merges. No persistent coding sessions.
